# ACL × Cedar (embedded) — direct per-resource grants (viewers/editors entity sets)
# Editors can also view (matches SpiceDB `view = viewer + editor`); a viewer cannot edit.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### ALLOW — persona has a direct viewer grant on this document
POST {{host}}/v1/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "engine": "cedar",
  "model": "acl",
  "principal": "psn-042051",
  "action": "acl.view",
  "resource_type": "AclDocument",
  "resource": "acldoc-000171"
}

### DENY — the same viewer is NOT an editor, so edit is refused
POST {{host}}/v1/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "engine": "cedar",
  "model": "acl",
  "principal": "psn-042051",
  "action": "acl.edit",
  "resource_type": "AclDocument",
  "resource": "acldoc-000171"
}

### Playground — try a persona with no grant at all (deny on both actions)
POST {{host}}/v1/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "engine": "cedar",
  "model": "acl",
  "principal": "psn-999999",
  "action": "acl.view",
  "resource_type": "AclDocument",
  "resource": "acldoc-000171"
}
